body:
This will allow us to use `nothing` in `∂x∂ξ` and still allow `transform` and `project` to work.

Changing `dual(axes(local_geometry.∂x∂ξ, 2))` to `ContravariantAxis{I}()` and `dual(axes(local_geometry.∂ξ∂x, 1)` to `CovariantAxis{I}()` will always be true, based on the definition of LocalGeometry:

```julia
struct LocalGeometry{I, C <: AbstractPoint, FT, ∂x∂ξT, ∂ξ∂xT, gⁱʲT, gᵢⱼT}
    ...
    ∂x∂ξ::∂x∂ξT #::Axis2Tensor{FT, Tuple{LocalAxis{I}, CovariantAxis{I}}, S}
    ∂ξ∂x::∂ξ∂xT #::Axis2Tensor{FT, Tuple{ContravariantAxis{I}, LocalAxis{I}}, S}
```
Note that we no longer strictly enforce these types (so that we can use `nothing` when they are unused), however they are the only non-nothing types supported.
